Key Match Events: David Brooks scored the opening goal for Wales just three minutes into the match
Neco Williams scored a free-kick to give Wales a 2-0 lead
Teemu Pukki scored a goal for Finland before half-time to make it 2-1
Brennan Johnson scored Wales' third goal after a defensive error by Finland
Daniel James scored Wales' fourth goal in the final minutes of the game
Others: Wales progressed to the play-off final where they will face Poland
The final will be played in Cardiff on March 26
The winner of the play-off final will join Netherlands, France, and Austria in Group D for Euro 2024
